<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920317-0121</DOCNO><DOCID>920317-0121.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Fibronics International Inc.:   Deficit Totaling $2.2 Million   Is Posted for Fourth Period</HL><DATE>03/17/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   FBRX</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><NS>EARNINGS (ERN)</NS><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Fibronics International Inc., citing inventory write-downsand high product introduction costs, reported afourth-quarter loss of $2.2 million, or 35 cents a share, onrevenue of $16 million.   In the year-ago quarter, the Hyannis, Mass., companyreported net income of $1.2 million, or 19 cents a share,after a $377,000 extraordinary credit for tax-losscarry-forwards. Revenue was $17 million.</LP><TEXT>   The maker of fiber optic data communications devices saidit introduced a significant number of complex, new productslast year that consumed greater than expected human resourcesand expense.   After taking into account its product introductiondifficulties, Fibronics said it wrote down the value of itsinventory by $1.5 million to $15.8 million.   In 1991, Fibronics had a loss of $3.3 million, or 52 centsa share, on revenue of $54 million. In 1990, it had netincome of $3.8 million, or 59 cents a share, after a $910,000extraordinary credit for tax-loss carry-forwards. Revenue was$63 million.</TEXT></DOC>